1
00:01:39,916 --> 00:01:42,646
Can you see better
if I move it a little closer?

2
00:01:43,119 --> 00:01:44,916
I can see something.

3
00:01:45,188 --> 00:01:48,715
It's parts of the grid, but it's still rotating.
It's not locking up.

4
00:01:48,792 --> 00:01:51,090
Maybe we all need a little break, Lillian.

5
00:01:51,161 --> 00:01:52,719
Hal, you take a break.

6
00:01:53,363 --> 00:01:55,331
Michael, we're almost there.

7
00:01:55,532 --> 00:01:56,931
How's that?

8
00:01:57,901 --> 00:02:00,734
It's better, but it's all scrambled.

9
00:02:02,605 --> 00:02:04,266
- How's that?
- It's better.

10
00:02:05,975 --> 00:02:07,306
How's the synch?

11
00:02:07,443 --> 00:02:09,775
Plus-25. Better?

12
00:02:10,914 --> 00:02:13,109
I can sort of make out part of the grid,
but it's...

13
00:02:13,716 --> 00:02:14,774
I don't know.

14
00:02:15,451 --> 00:02:17,544
Maybe something's wrong with the grid.

15
00:02:17,754 --> 00:02:20,655
Hal, kill the grid.
And, Gordy, take a look around the lab.

16
00:02:28,398 --> 00:02:30,366
Oh, this is weird.

17
00:02:31,401 --> 00:02:33,164
Try something else.

18
00:02:34,003 --> 00:02:35,402
How's that?

19
00:02:36,239 --> 00:02:39,834
It's an image of the lab, but it's rotating.
It's all out of phase.

20
00:02:46,583 --> 00:02:48,050
I think I've got it.

21
00:02:48,184 --> 00:02:50,175
Gordy, go back to the grid for a second.

22
00:02:56,593 --> 00:02:58,788
A little more phase compensator.

23
00:02:59,229 --> 00:03:00,696
Up the synch signal.

24
00:03:01,130 --> 00:03:02,722
What do you see, angel?

25
00:03:02,932 --> 00:03:04,399
Clockwise rotation.

26
00:03:04,534 --> 00:03:06,399
It's still all scrambled.

27
00:03:07,370 --> 00:03:09,361
Okay, just a little more.

28
00:03:09,639 --> 00:03:12,107
Hold it a second. I think I got it.

29
00:03:13,543 --> 00:03:15,602
Hey, there it is! You got it.

30
00:03:15,845 --> 00:03:17,403
Okay, Hal, let's slate it.

31
00:03:17,513 --> 00:03:19,708
Gordy, follow Hal around with the slate.

32
00:03:27,357 --> 00:03:29,188
Hal, get the slate in there.

33
00:03:29,425 --> 00:03:30,585
I got it.

34
00:03:31,194 --> 00:03:32,684
Hold it one minute.

35
00:03:58,321 --> 00:03:59,811
Okay. Slate it.

36
00:04:11,367 --> 00:04:12,698
We've got speed.

37
00:04:12,769 --> 00:04:15,602
Test, October 11th, 10:41 p. m. Mark.

38
00:04:21,411 --> 00:04:22,844
To the kitchen.

39
00:04:22,912 --> 00:04:24,675
Good idea. Let's eat.

40
00:04:37,260 --> 00:04:38,818
Lou, what do you got for me?

41
00:04:38,895 --> 00:04:40,886
Here you go, Gordy. Everything you said.

42
00:04:40,964 --> 00:04:42,556
- Slating.
- It's all bad.

43
00:04:42,765 --> 00:04:43,891
Hot and cold...

44
00:04:43,967 --> 00:04:45,195
...sweet and sour...

45
00:04:45,435 --> 00:04:48,097
...chewy and melt-in-your-mouth bad!

46
00:04:48,237 --> 00:04:50,000
Let's try something exotic.

47
00:04:50,173 --> 00:04:51,663
You name it, Gordy.

48
00:04:52,809 --> 00:04:53,969
A little steak.

49
00:04:54,043 --> 00:04:55,840
A little steak comin' up.

50
00:04:55,912 --> 00:04:57,174
Peanut butter.

51
00:04:57,480 --> 00:04:58,674
Peanut butter.

52
00:04:59,082 --> 00:05:00,674
Hot fudge!

53
00:05:01,184 --> 00:05:02,446
Hot fudge?

54
00:05:02,552 --> 00:05:04,110
A few nuts.

55
00:05:05,888 --> 00:05:07,617
And some marshmallow sauce.

56
00:05:08,391 --> 00:05:09,983
Marshmallow sauce.

57
00:05:10,093 --> 00:05:11,720
And put a cherry on top.

58
00:05:12,395 --> 00:05:14,795
Man, marshmallow and cherry on steak?

59
00:05:15,932 --> 00:05:18,230
What in the world have you been drinkin'?

60
00:05:18,868 --> 00:05:20,768
What's he been smokin'?

61
00:05:36,019 --> 00:05:38,453
Hey, spaceman,
welcome back to the planet Earth.

62
00:05:38,654 --> 00:05:42,317
What you see before you is the latest
fashion in full sensory gratification.

63
00:05:42,392 --> 00:05:43,859
- Now, come on, give us a kiss.
- No.

64
00:05:43,926 --> 00:05:45,018
- Come on.
- No!

65
00:05:45,094 --> 00:05:46,584
Come on, let's go back to work.

66
00:05:46,662 --> 00:05:48,220
- Gordy, go on!
- For science.

67
00:05:48,297 --> 00:05:50,162
Gordy, try to contain yourself.

68
00:05:50,700 --> 00:05:52,395
This is a test.

69
00:05:54,537 --> 00:05:57,734
Andrea, give us a 90 DBF
in sine wave, please.

70
00:05:58,007 --> 00:05:59,372
Okay, I'm ready.

71
00:06:02,345 --> 00:06:03,334
Slate.

72
00:06:22,398 --> 00:06:24,593
Gordy, this is not on our itinerary.

73
00:06:24,834 --> 00:06:27,359
Just a few seconds. I think I got an idea.

74
00:06:27,470 --> 00:06:28,664
Well, hi, Hal. How are you?

75
00:06:28,771 --> 00:06:30,363
What are you guys up to, anyway?

76
00:06:30,673 --> 00:06:32,607
Just wanna see my old buddy, Lena.

77
00:06:37,013 --> 00:06:38,708
How are you, Lena, honey?

78
00:06:41,384 --> 00:06:44,785
Lena, I know what it's like
to be guinea pig.

79
00:06:53,896 --> 00:06:56,126
Is her output on standard interface?

80
00:06:57,100 --> 00:06:58,294
Regular plug.

81
00:07:01,471 --> 00:07:02,836
I don't know...

82
00:07:04,273 --> 00:07:06,036
Perfect mate for Dr. Brace.

83
00:07:06,142 --> 00:07:08,440
I don't know if that's such a good idea.

84
00:07:09,912 --> 00:07:12,403
- That's not so funny, Gordy.
- Come in, Lena.

85
00:07:42,345 --> 00:07:43,642
What did you do?

86
00:07:43,746 --> 00:07:46,874
Nothing. Just a little experiment
in animal behavior.

87
00:07:51,787 --> 00:07:54,483
There's something wrong with you.
You know that?

88
00:07:55,491 --> 00:07:57,015
You didn't like Lena.

89
00:07:57,260 --> 00:07:58,921
- What happened?
- Nothing.

90
00:08:00,596 --> 00:08:01,620
So?

91
00:08:01,697 --> 00:08:03,392
I'm telling you, it works!

92
00:08:03,466 --> 00:08:05,457
The tests? Sound, taste...?

93
00:08:05,735 --> 00:08:08,499
Everything, everything.
One hundred percent. In fact, better.

94
00:08:08,604 --> 00:08:09,866
Well, what did you taste?

95
00:08:09,939 --> 00:08:11,930
Steak, overdone. Right?

96
00:08:12,008 --> 00:08:15,671
Peanut butter, hot fudge sauce,
slight orange flavor.

97
00:08:15,945 --> 00:08:17,708
- Disgusting.
- Nuts?

98
00:08:17,947 --> 00:08:19,778
Walnuts. I hate them.

99
00:08:20,650 --> 00:08:21,878
That's it?

100
00:08:22,385 --> 00:08:23,818
Marshmallow...

101
00:08:23,886 --> 00:08:26,116
- Cherry on the top.
- That's it man!

102
00:08:26,589 --> 00:08:27,817
How do you feel now?

103
00:08:27,890 --> 00:08:30,757
I feel like a glass of champagne.
Get some glasses.

104
00:08:32,295 --> 00:08:33,694
Congratulations.

105
00:08:35,064 --> 00:08:36,053
What's this?

106
00:08:36,132 --> 00:08:37,463
One lousy beer.

107
00:08:39,402 --> 00:08:41,302
I would like to make a toast.

108
00:08:41,938 --> 00:08:43,963
To the one who never gives up...

109
00:08:45,808 --> 00:08:47,366
...Lillian Reynolds...

110
00:08:47,643 --> 00:08:50,976
...E. E., M. D., Ph. D...

111
00:08:53,082 --> 00:08:54,515
...B. M. T...

112
00:08:55,451 --> 00:08:58,011
...B. V. D., R. S. V. P., C. O. D.

113
00:08:59,455 --> 00:09:00,752
My friend.

114
00:09:02,925 --> 00:09:04,187
Cheers.

115
00:09:05,795 --> 00:09:06,887
Cheers.

116
00:09:43,566 --> 00:09:44,624
'Night.

117
00:11:02,578 --> 00:11:03,840
Hi, Dad.

118
00:11:04,146 --> 00:11:05,477
Hi, Mike.

119
00:11:05,715 --> 00:11:08,479
You worked late.
Did you have a good day?

120
00:11:09,652 --> 00:11:10,812
Hello, Barry.

121
00:11:50,626 --> 00:11:51,786
Success.

122
00:11:52,561 --> 00:11:53,721
We made it.

123
00:12:04,373 --> 00:12:06,273
Talented man, your husband.

124
00:12:06,609 --> 00:12:08,941
Impossible at times, but talented.

125
00:12:09,612 --> 00:12:11,170
What do you think? Can you handle it?

126
00:12:11,280 --> 00:12:15,114
Yes, I think I can.
I think I can get it down to size...

127
00:12:15,284 --> 00:12:17,047
...and make it look attractive.

128
00:12:17,353 --> 00:12:19,082
Maybe something like...

129
00:12:19,355 --> 00:12:20,788
...stereo headphones.

130
00:12:20,956 --> 00:12:23,117
Oh, I'm not worried about that.
I know you can.

131
00:12:23,192 --> 00:12:24,318
It's Michael.

132
00:12:25,728 --> 00:12:28,196
You're gonna have to work
very closely with him.

133
00:12:28,831 --> 00:12:30,196
Is that a problem?

134
00:12:30,366 --> 00:12:31,333
No.

135
00:12:31,867 --> 00:12:34,028
- That won't be any problem.
- Good.

136
00:12:34,170 --> 00:12:35,068
Not for me.

137
00:12:36,138 --> 00:12:38,163
Hal, I'm gonna kill you after this.

138
00:12:38,240 --> 00:12:40,037
Lillian, you don't understand.
It's part of my...

139
00:12:40,276 --> 00:12:43,211
- What are you upset about?
- It's gonna be slow and agonizing.

140
00:12:43,279 --> 00:12:45,941
It's not part of your job.
I know what you wanted to do.

141
00:12:46,115 --> 00:12:47,810
You wanted to grease yourself
with the boss.

142
00:12:47,883 --> 00:12:48,611
I did not.

143
00:12:48,684 --> 00:12:50,982
Why don't you wait and see
what he has to say?

144
00:12:51,554 --> 00:12:53,647
Why don't you grow up!

145
00:12:55,825 --> 00:12:57,156
Be careful.

146
00:13:00,596 --> 00:13:01,995
I hate this junk!

147
00:13:04,900 --> 00:13:06,299
Hello, Michael.

148
00:13:06,635 --> 00:13:08,227
Good to see you.

149
00:13:08,471 --> 00:13:09,836
- Lillian.
- Hi, Alex. How are you?

150
00:13:13,209 --> 00:13:14,870
Well, won't you sit down?

151
00:13:19,248 --> 00:13:20,180
Well...

152
00:13:20,282 --> 00:13:21,510
...congratulations.

153
00:13:21,617 --> 00:13:22,709
For what?

154
00:13:23,686 --> 00:13:25,517
Hal said you had a breakthrough.

155
00:13:27,590 --> 00:13:28,887
Well, Hal's crazy.

156
00:13:31,560 --> 00:13:33,619
Did you have a breakthrough or not?

157
00:13:35,998 --> 00:13:36,987
Yes.

158
00:13:40,269 --> 00:13:44,569
Alex, dear, it was just another test.
A little better, but still crude.

159
00:13:45,474 --> 00:13:46,941
What's the big problem?

160
00:13:47,810 --> 00:13:51,246
The superconductors have to be chilled
to 270 below to work.

161
00:13:51,814 --> 00:13:53,941
The whole thing is too big and heavy.

162
00:13:54,850 --> 00:13:58,616
Your hotshots, Evans and Wetmore,
failed on that one year after year.

163
00:14:04,326 --> 00:14:06,351
Courtesy, Evans-Wetmore.

164
00:14:09,999 --> 00:14:12,866
It's a superconducting chip.
No cooling needed.

165
00:14:13,969 --> 00:14:15,368
When did they do this?

166
00:14:15,838 --> 00:14:16,896
You need it...

167
00:14:16,972 --> 00:14:18,200
...it's yours.

168
00:14:18,574 --> 00:14:19,768
Keep it quiet.

169
00:14:19,842 --> 00:14:22,333
Data processing division
will go right through the roof...

170
00:14:22,444 --> 00:14:25,379
...with the high-speed
computer applications of that thing.

171
00:14:25,447 --> 00:14:28,712
Karen has expressed enthusiasm
to help us market it and package it.

172
00:14:28,784 --> 00:14:31,082
Alex, I think you're moving too fast.

173
00:14:31,787 --> 00:14:33,482
You haven't even seen it yet.

174
00:14:34,089 --> 00:14:37,183
There's more to it
than just practical applications...

175
00:14:37,493 --> 00:14:38,687
...and packaging.

176
00:14:40,462 --> 00:14:41,486
Lillian...

177
00:14:42,932 --> 00:14:44,297
...I know you can do it.

178
00:14:45,768 --> 00:14:47,167
I know you can do it.

179
00:14:49,204 --> 00:14:51,104
I'd like a demonstration.

180
00:14:51,407 --> 00:14:52,874
I want you...

181
00:14:53,375 --> 00:14:56,970
...to knock my socks off. Okay?

182
00:15:02,785 --> 00:15:03,774
Good!

183
00:15:06,655 --> 00:15:07,747
And thanks.

184
00:15:07,957 --> 00:15:09,322
Don't lose that.

185
00:15:12,094 --> 00:15:13,925
You did it again, Alex.

186
00:15:15,264 --> 00:15:16,253
Thank you.

187
00:15:16,398 --> 00:15:18,525
Any problem working with Karen?

188
00:15:21,904 --> 00:15:23,929
No. Not for me.

189
00:15:25,808 --> 00:15:26,832
Thanks, Mike.

190
00:15:34,850 --> 00:15:37,182
I told you to get out of the pool.
He pays no attention.

191
00:15:37,252 --> 00:15:38,651
I'll get him, honey.

192
00:15:41,657 --> 00:15:42,885
Hurry up!

193
00:15:45,127 --> 00:15:48,153
Dr. Brace, I'd like to introduce
Dr. Harris and Dr. Bock.

194
00:15:48,297 --> 00:15:49,662
Call me Ted.

195
00:15:53,736 --> 00:15:55,067
You saw the house before.

196
00:15:55,304 --> 00:15:57,704
Yeah, yeah, we're sold.
We just want to get all the details.

197
00:15:57,806 --> 00:15:59,797
- We signed all the papers today.
- Good.

198
00:15:59,908 --> 00:16:01,671
- That's for you.
- Hey, Dad, is that it?

199
00:16:01,810 --> 00:16:04,574
- That's what you wanted.
- All right. You got the right one.

200
00:16:05,581 --> 00:16:07,048
Say thank you.

201
00:16:10,085 --> 00:16:11,382
As you can see...

202
00:16:12,988 --> 00:16:15,149
...this is a very special house.

203
00:16:17,092 --> 00:16:19,185
I spent a lot of time to get it right.

204
00:16:21,964 --> 00:16:23,932
Why don't you show them
the secret closet?

205
00:16:23,999 --> 00:16:25,694
Good idea. Right this way.

206
00:16:25,801 --> 00:16:29,464
The house is wonderful. Ted loves
all the special things you've done.

207
00:16:31,573 --> 00:16:33,097
Do you like them?

208
00:16:33,409 --> 00:16:34,433
No.

209
00:16:35,944 --> 00:16:37,912
- It's theirs now.
- I know.

210
00:16:41,483 --> 00:16:43,075
I can't stay here now.

211
00:16:44,286 --> 00:16:46,277
Oh, well, that's okay. I can...

212
00:16:46,588 --> 00:16:49,148
...take care of all the packing and stuff.

213
00:16:49,692 --> 00:16:51,091
- You sure?
- Sure.

214
00:16:51,160 --> 00:16:52,889
It's a lot to do.

215
00:16:53,796 --> 00:16:55,593
Do you have cardboard boxes?

216
00:16:56,198 --> 00:16:58,029
Yes, I have cardboard boxes.

217
00:16:58,801 --> 00:17:01,235
I can take care of it all. Don't worry.

218
00:17:04,006 --> 00:17:06,236
You could go live over at the center.

219
00:17:06,308 --> 00:17:07,639
Lillian's there.

220
00:17:15,718 --> 00:17:17,618
This is Flight Simulation Lab Control.

221
00:17:17,786 --> 00:17:19,276
Sold your house yet?

222
00:17:21,023 --> 00:17:22,012
Yep.

223
00:17:23,625 --> 00:17:26,560
I keep telling you
the rooms at the center are so cheap.

224
00:17:26,628 --> 00:17:27,595
I know.

225
00:17:27,996 --> 00:17:33,332
At 9:38 p. m. pilot Gordon Forbes is
performing a low-level simulated assault.

226
00:17:35,838 --> 00:17:38,534
Range: 100 yards and closing.

227
00:17:40,375 --> 00:17:41,672
Ninety-five.

228
00:17:42,878 --> 00:17:46,245
Ninety. Simulated altitude, 60 feet.

229
00:17:47,116 --> 00:17:49,311
Ground speed, 512 knots.

230
00:17:50,052 --> 00:17:53,180
Assault range, 85.

231
00:17:54,590 --> 00:17:55,682
Eighty.

232
00:17:56,191 --> 00:17:58,591
It's not worth it, Gordy! Don't do it!

233
00:18:01,697 --> 00:18:03,130
Pilot Forbes, you're...

234
00:18:03,198 --> 00:18:05,098
...off of the simulation.

235
00:18:05,267 --> 00:18:06,962
Sweet target in sight.

236
00:18:08,971 --> 00:18:10,734
Dr. Reynolds, Dr. Brace...

237
00:18:10,806 --> 00:18:13,502
...your pilot has lost control.

238
00:18:18,347 --> 00:18:19,279
Ready.

239
00:18:19,348 --> 00:18:20,645
- Helmet's on?
- Yeah.

240
00:18:20,749 --> 00:18:22,614
Contact. Okay, let's get in.

241
00:18:23,685 --> 00:18:25,118
How's that? Okay.

242
00:18:25,554 --> 00:18:27,181
Give me the seat belts.

243
00:18:27,289 --> 00:18:28,984
Okay, Gordy. Hit it.

244
00:18:30,092 --> 00:18:31,719
Great gas pedal. Let's go!

245
00:18:39,201 --> 00:18:40,532
Come on, Gordy!

246
00:18:44,239 --> 00:18:46,571
Yeah, I'm comin'. Wait a minute.

247
00:18:46,842 --> 00:18:48,776
Tallyho! Here we go!

248
00:18:50,579 --> 00:18:53,810
- I'm gonna die. I'm freezing!
- You're gonna make history!

249
00:18:53,982 --> 00:18:58,180
- It's a little chilly. It's gonna be great!
- I don't wanna go! It's too cold!

250
00:19:04,326 --> 00:19:06,260
Come on. One more time for science.

251
00:19:06,328 --> 00:19:08,888
It's gonna rain, Gordy. Let's go home!

252
00:19:08,964 --> 00:19:11,592
- Too cold. It's not even...
- Come on, come on.

253
00:19:11,667 --> 00:19:13,567
We're gonna do it. Come on, get in.

254
00:19:32,888 --> 00:19:35,618
Nobody is gonna put a thing like that
on their head.

255
00:19:35,691 --> 00:19:38,660
It's gotta be pared down
to the absolute essentials.

256
00:19:38,760 --> 00:19:42,161
Just enough to house the sensors.
You know, it can't look intimidating.

257
00:19:42,231 --> 00:19:44,358
What do I care what it looks like!

258
00:19:49,738 --> 00:19:51,103
Put a chip here...

259
00:19:51,406 --> 00:19:52,771
...another here...

260
00:19:53,342 --> 00:19:54,400
...here...

261
00:19:54,910 --> 00:19:58,107
...an op. Amp, spread flat across.
That's all. Just do it.

262
00:19:58,213 --> 00:20:00,613
- Put the rest of the stuff remote.
- Sure.

263
00:20:20,102 --> 00:20:21,399
How's that?

264
00:20:21,803 --> 00:20:22,963
It's good.

